auction,  or  we  should  delay  the  transition  date.  That  either  one  is 
going  to  cost  the  taxpayers  money,  in  my  opinion,  in  the  long  run. 
Because if we don’t get the money from the auction, we’re going to 
have  to  pay  back  the  money  you’ve  borrowed  from  the  Treasury. 
And that’s going to be a real battle up here, I think. 

What  about  the  converter  box  program?  As  I  said,  that  is  basi-
cally  going  to  be  financed  by  the  auction.  What  are  you  doing  now 
