23 

Mr.  KNEUER.  The  coupon  program  is  designed  to  reach  all  of 
those  kinds  of  consumers.  With  regards  to  retailers,  we  want  to 
make  sure  that  we  have  an  outreach  to  retailers  that  goes  beyond 
just  the  big  nationwide  chains  and  the  large  consumer  electronics. 
So,  we’ve  allowed  for  retailer  participation  from  mail-order,  over 
the  Internet,  as  well  as  traditional  brick-and-mortar,  and  we’ve 
also required that the vendor who’s going to fulfill the coupon pro-
gram for us has a plan to reach out to some of those nontraditional 
retailers  to  make  sure  that  the  same  sorts  of  retailers  that  your 
constituents  rely  on  for  all  of  their  day-to-day  needs  will  also  be 
able to participate in the coupon program. 

